law.text:
Public institutions of higher education shall:
Provide postsecondary education to students;
Transmit culture and extend knowledge through general higher education;
Teach and train students for careers and advanced study;
Protect academic freedom;
Promote civic responsibility;
Enhance economic development of the State through research, training, and extension services to business and industry;
Provide public services for citizens of the State; and
Assure that women and minorities are equitably represented among faculty, staff, and administration, so that the higher education community reflects the diversity of the State's population.
